decks.notes: The deck is centered around assembling the combo of Doomsday and Thassa's Oracle to win the game. It includes a variety of card draw and selection spells such as Ponder and Brainstorm to set up the combo quickly. The deck also has disruption in the form of Force of Will and Flusterstorm to protect the combo from opposing interaction. With the ability to quickly assemble its win condition and protect it, this deck aims to win the game before the opponent can react effectively.

This deck focuses on deploying aggressive creatures while disrupting opponents with hate cards like Thorn of Amethyst and Trinisphere. The deck aims to control the board with creatures like Thalia, Guardian of Thraben and Archon of Emeria, making it difficult for the opponent to cast spells efficiently. In addition, the deck utilizes cards like Swords to Plowshares for removal and Chalice of the Void for further disruption. With mana acceleration from Moxen and other fast mana sources, the deck can quickly establish its board presence and overwhelm opponents with its aggressive hatebear strategy.
